From 7234b761770fa98248d16935714965ac4078075e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi-Wei Wang <yiweiw@nvidia.com>
Date: Fri, 23 Aug 2024 14:04:24 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 70/95] NVIDIA: SAUCE: pwm: tegra: Avoid overflow on 100% duty
 cycle

Bits[31:16] are reserved for PWM field of Tegra264 PWM controller, so
the PWM ranges from 0 to 65535. To avoid the overflow happening when
the calculated PWM is 65536, this change decrements it by 1 before
programming to PWM field.

http://nvbugs/4545733
http://nvbugs/4748816

Upstream-Status: Backport
Signed-off-by: Yi-Wei Wang <yiweiw@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Laxman Dewangan <ldewangan@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Noah Wager <noah.wager@canonical.com>
Acked-by: Jacob Martin <jacob.martin@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Noah Wager <noah.wager@canonical.com>
(cherry picked from commit bb9ab2ba7fdf65cd6790f5328025b8c97ea2e2f2)
Signed-off-by: Matt Madison <matt@madison.systems>
---
 drivers/pwm/pwm-tegra.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/pwm/pwm-tegra.c b/drivers/pwm/pwm-tegra.c
index 6acf3a9bb214..c98e9fb5343c 100644
--- a/drivers/pwm/pwm-tegra.c
+++ b/drivers/pwm/pwm-tegra.c
@@ -91,6 +91,7 @@
 
 #define DEFAULT_PWM_DEPTH 255
 #define PWM_ENABLE	(1 << 31)
+#define REG_WIDTH 32
 
 struct tegra_pwm_soc {
 	unsigned int channel_offset;
@@ -169,6 +170,11 @@ static int tegra_pwm_config(struct pwm_chip *chip, struct pwm_device *pwm,
 	pwm_f = (u32)DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST_ULL(duty_ns * (1 + pc->pwm_depth),
 					   period_ns);
 
+	/* Avoid overflow on 100% duty cycle */
+	if (pwm_f == 1 + pc->pwm_depth)
+		if (duty_s + duty_w == REG_WIDTH)
+			--pwm_f;
+
 	/*
 	 * required_clk_rate is a reference rate for source clock and
 	 * it is derived based on user requested period.
-- 
2.43.0

